eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.ranking

Class NoRandomAccessRanking

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.ranking.NoRandomAccessRanking
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IRankAggregator

    public class NoRandomAccessRanking
extends Object
implements IRankAggregator
    Progressively computes ranked aggregated results according to the No Random Access algorithm.

    • Constructor Detail

      • NoRandomAccessRanking

        public NoRandomAccessRanking(Map<String,DatasetIdentifier> datasetIdentifiers,
                             Map<String,Map<?,?>> lookups,
                             Map<String,ISimilarity> similarities,
                             Map<String,Double[]> weights,
                             Map<String,INormal> normalizations,
                             Map<String,Thread> tasks,
                             Map<String,ConcurrentLinkedQueue<PartialResult>> queues,
                             Map<String,AtomicBoolean> runControl,
                             int topk,
                             Logger log)
        Constructor
        Parameters:
        datasetIdentifiers - List of the attributes involved in similarity search queries.
        lookups - Dictionary of the various data collections involved in the similarity search queries.
        similarities - Dictionary of the similarity measures applied in each search query.
        weights - Dictionary of the (possibly multiple alternative) weights per attribute to be applied in scoring the final results.
        normalizations - Dictionary of normalization functions to be applied in data values during random access.
        tasks - The collection of running threads; each one executes a query and it is associated with its respective queue that collects its results.
        queues - The collection of the queues collecting results from each search query.
        runControl - The collection of boolean values indicating the status of each thread.
        topk - The count of ranked aggregated results to collect, i.e., those with the top-k (highest) aggregated similarity scores.
        log - Handle to the log file for notifications and execution statistics.

      • issueRankedResult

        private boolean issueRankedResult(int i,
                                  int w,
                                  String item,
                                  double score,
                                  boolean exact)
        Inserts the i-th ranked result to the output list. Rank is based on the overall score; ties in scores are resolved arbitrarily.
        Parameters:
        i - The rank to the assigned to the output result.
        w - The identifier of the weight combination to be applied on the scores.
        item - The original identifier of this item in the dataset
        score - The overall (weighted) score of this result.
        exact - Boolean indicating whether the ranking of this result is exact or not.
        Returns:
        A Boolean value: True, if extra result(s) have been issued; otherwise, False.
